{
  "stem": "27335.9",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, concerning the survivors of Budapest, that is the-- that is the-- this old wives' story about Raoul Wallenberg who was introduced to-- introduced first in Hungary, to-- whom I could never find out.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But there is a book written by Levai, Eugene Levai, a Hungarian-Jewish-- Jewish writer.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "He wrote a book about that.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And all the stories, the Jews by the tens of thousands of them were saved by Raoul Wallenberg.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And then the story got into the United States, and the whole scores of books, newspapers, and magazine articles, and I, I, I have file here.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "It may be a six-inch, six-inch thick, all about Wallenberg, newspaper clippings and so on and so forth.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "What this Wallenberg did to the Jews but-- back in Hungary, in my, in my research for my book that I wrote, and I have a chapter about the Wallenberg case, I tried to find a one single person who would have-- who would have state definitely, consciously, that Raoul Wallenberg saved me.",
      "word_count": 53
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "In the way as it's written in the book.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Or I tried to find one single copy of the, of the schutzpass, as-- as they called it, they called it in-- in German, they gave to Wallenberg, so-called Wallenberg passport, that saved.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "One.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "I looked all over Budapest, [INAUDIBLE], Jewish people.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Nobody could produce me one.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "But my god.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "There should be one at least who saved it.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "At least one saved it as souvenir that is what saved my life.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "Not one single, single copy of the schutzpass, because it was all, all just a-- just a mish-mash.",
      "word_count": 18
    }
  ],
